
	Recursion: When a calls itself
	
	Recursion creates a loop
	
	Recursive function has two parts
		Recursive call(s)
		Base condition
	
	3! = 3 x 2!
	4! = 4 x 3!
	5! = 5 x 4!
	
	n! = n x (n-1)!
	
	1 + 2 + 3 + 4 + ... + n
	
	Seed values
	
	0, 1, 1, 2, 3, 5, 8, ...
	1, 1, 2, 3, 5, 8, ...
	
	fib(n) = fib(n-1) + fib(n-2)
	
	O(n^2)		-	Terrible
	O(n logn)	-	Bad
	
	
	linked-list insertion	-	function
